## Version Centralization Requirements

**CRITICAL**: All Redis/Jedis versions MUST be centralized. Never hardcode versions.

### DO: Use Version Catalog

```toml
# gradle/libs.versions.toml
[versions]
bitso-commons-redis = "4.2.1"
jedis4-utils = "3.0.0"

[libraries]
bitso-commons-redis = { module = "com.bitso.commons:redis", version.ref = "bitso-commons-redis" }
jedis4-utils = { module = "com.bitso.commons:jedis4-utils", version.ref = "jedis4-utils" }
```

```groovy
// build.gradle
dependencies {
    implementation libs.bitso.commons.redis
    implementation libs.jedis4.utils
}
```

### DON'T: Hardcode Versions

```groovy
// ❌ NEVER do this - causes version drift and upgrade failures
dependencies {
    implementation "com.bitso.commons:redis:3.1.0"
    implementation "com.bitso.commons:jedis4-utils:1.4.1"
}
```

